<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12005l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12005l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12005l"> 5(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> destroyed for building / rlway or <font face="wake">N</font> / or treasure / crock of gold</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>La destruction</mark> de ces monuments peut &ecirc;tre attribu&eacute;e &agrave; deux causes: d&apos;abord &agrave; la cupidit&eacute; stupide de ces Vandales modernes qui les abattent <mark>pour construire une grange ou empierrer un chemin</mark>; ensuite &agrave; la cr&eacute;dulit&eacute; publique. Cette cr&eacute;dulit&eacute; repose sur <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> la pr&eacute;tendue existence d&apos;<mark>un tr&eacute;sor</mark>.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Ici, c&apos;est une barrique d&apos;argent ou <mark>des tonneaux d&apos;or</mark>; l&agrave;, des coffres pr&eacute;cieux ou des diamants d&apos;un prix infini. <br><font color="green">[The destruction of these monuments can be attributed to two causes: first the stupid greed of these modern Vandals who raze them in order to build a barn or to pave a road; and also to the public&apos;s credulity. This credulity rests on [&hellip;]</font> the imagined existence of a treasure.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Here, it is a cask of silver or crock of gold, there a treasure-chest or diamonds of a price beyond compare.] <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 18</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
